<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n09119b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09119b">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09119b"> 119(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> jews sawed Greeks / asunder, ate flesh / licked blood ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">In Cyrene they <font color="green">[the Jews]</font> massacred 220,000 <mark>Greeks</mark>; in Cypress 240,000; in Egypt a very great multitude. Many of these unhappy victims <mark>were sawn asunder</mark>, according to a precedent to which David had given the sanction of his example. The victorious <mark>Jews devoured the flesh, licked up the blood</mark>, and twisted the entrails like a girdle round their bodies. See Dion Cassius, l. lxviii. <font color="green">[c. 32]</font> p. 11145. <small> Edward Gibbon, <a name="EGDF2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EGDF2"><cite title="source">Decline and Fall of the Roman Empire</cite></a> (ed. unknown) II, 222n (Chapter XVI)</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
